const String appPermissionsText = '''
Internet Access: CalPal utilizes an internet connection to retrieve the latest calorie data and securely store users' encrypted calorie information in the cloud. This enables convenient synchronization of calorie logs across multiple devices, ensuring seamless access and data consistency.

Camera Access: The app requires access to your device's camera to capture and identify food items. This feature assists in accurate calorie tracking and nutritional analysis by visually recognizing and cataloging consumed meals.

Microphone Access: CalPal's need for microphone access is tied to Android's camera access limitations. It's important to note that the app doesn't utilize the microphone for recording or any purpose unrelated to the camera. This access is solely integrated with the camera function and doesn't involve audio recording or processing.

Storage Access: By requesting access to your device's storage, CalPal can analyze images from your gallery. This permission enables the app to accurately detect food items in images, facilitating seamless integration with the calorie tracking feature.

At CalPal, the utmost priority is ensuring user data security and privacy. Each permission is used purposefully to enrich the app's functionalities, providing users with a comprehensive and secure calorie tracking experience while respecting their privacy.
''';
